Comment: Project by ministry of agriculture. Technical issues. Water does not stay in dam. Big flood damaged the dam as not constructed very well.
Water ponding in the wadi floor downstream of the dam.

Channel eroded through very friable orange rhyolite. Dyke running through the dam aligment, possibly the design assumed the dyke would prevent erosion around the sides of the structure. Project started in 2016 and finished in 2020.  The flows deposited the sediment behind the dam a few days before we came.  Also sediment deposited in 2020. When the dam failed in 2020 they sent letter to Ministry of Environment but nothing done to remediate the structure. No sediment behind the dam when it was first built.
Water in the wells behind dam less salty than downstream according to the Sub-Director of the Ministry of Agriculture. Since dam built water became less salty downstream, anacdotaly.
Creator: GWPConsultants

Comment: Borehole.  Meant to give water to Dasbyo but did not work. Instead they drilled another downstream and piped it.  80-90m deep. Normally they go no deeper than 60m as the salinity gets too high (3000us/cm). The garden on the other side of the wadi has its own well.
Creator: GWPConsultants

Comment: 10 or 12 water distribution points like this in Dasbyo. BH pumps to reservoir on the hill which supplies the water points. They fill the reservoir once a week (Sat. or Fri.).  Somebody has to go to the pump to start them (7-10km away).  Opened once a week and have water for 7 days. Last opened on Saturday. When the water is turned on the residents take the water to their houses and the reservoir is empty by midweek. The water in the reservoir is salty. When woman drink the water their skin gets sores and they can lose their babies. 200 households (8-15 people per household) in villages.  Pipes used to reduce walking distance.  Sometimes the pump battery fails and the reservoir is broken for a month.
Creator: GWPConsultants

Comment: Pumping house. Reservoir is 4x4x2m.  Water pumped to the reservoir.  Pump two of these reservoirs to the upper reservoir. e.g. half fill upper reservoir.  Borehole pump is 4kw. Surface pump is 4kw.  Sub-Director from the Ministry of Agriculture in Ali sabieh is responsible for maintainanace. Yield of 10m3/h. Yield does not decrease in the summer.  Pumped since 1991.  Grenfos mk ii pump.
Creator: GWPConsultants

Comment: View of Holhol.  The old train used to be used for bringing water. 1 borehole gives 20% of water.  half of that went to the military base.  this well is located near the refugee camp.  Shallow Wells unproductive after drought.  Study to create BH for new train construction.  outcome of this was BHs in hindi.

Comment: Reservoir filled by water from the BH. It takes two hours to fill. Once full the water is sent to Holhol.  They empty the reservoir entirely. This is the only reservoir at Hindi except for school reservoir. Every day two reservoirs full are sent to Holhol and then the reservoir is partially filled for to supply Hindi. 7x7m reservoir. Approx. 2m high.
